  "intent_precise": "4. Illumina DNA Prep - Clean Up Libraries: Using mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot PCR plate), reagent_plate (plate, slot reagent plate), clean PCR plate (pcr_plate, slot 1), reservoir (reservoir, slot 2). With temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (2) Disengage magnets to release beads. (3) Pause: \n\n\n\nReplace 200ul filtertipracks before resuming.\n\n\n\n (4) Engage magnets for bead separation. (5) Transfer from source to liquid_trash A1. (6) Transfer from source to destination. (7) Disengage magnets to release beads. (8) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (9) Transfer from source to destination. (10) Wait 2 seconds. (11) Pause for incubation. (12) Engage magnets for bead separation. (13) Pause for incubation. (14) Engage magnets for bead separation. (15) Incubate for 5 minutes. (16) Transfer from source to destination. (17) Wait 2 seconds. (18) Disengage magnets to release beads. (19) Transfer from source to destination. (20) Wait 2 seconds. (21) Mix 5 times at 30\u00b5L. (22) Transfer from source to destination. (23) Mix reps_mix times. (24) Wait 2 seconds. (25) Pause: Move the PCR plate on slot 1 to the magnetic module. Place a clean PCR plate in slot 1. (26) Mix reps_mix times at 10\u00b5L. (27) Transfer from source to destination. (28) Wait 2 seconds. (29) Pause for incubation. (30) Engage magnets for bead separation. (31) Pause for incubation. (32) Transfer from source to destination. (33) Mix reps_mix times. (34) Wait 2 seconds. (35) Disengage magnets to release beads. (36) Pause: Move PCR plate from slot 1 to magnetic module. Place a clean plate in slot 1. (37) Incubate for 5 minutes. (38) Engage magnets for bead separation. (39) Pause for incubation. (40) Incubate for 5 minutes. (41) Disengage magnets to release beads. (42) Transfer from source to destination. (43) Mix 3 times. (44) Wait 2 seconds. (45) Incubate for 5 minutes. (46) Engage magnets for bead separation. (47) Incubate for 5 minutes. (48) Transfer from source to destination. (49) Wait 2 seconds. (50) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C). (volumes 10\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~27 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Illumina DNA Prep library cleanup, start by setting up your mag plate on the PCR slot, reagent plate on the reagent slot, clean PCR plate in slot 1, and reservoir in slot 2, then cool the temperature module to 4\u00b0C and disengage the magnets to release the beads. You'll need to pause to replace the 200\u00b5L filter tip racks before proceeding with the magnetic separation and transfer steps. The protocol involves multiple rounds of bead washing with 200\u00b5L transfers, mixing cycles (including 5 times at 30\u00b5L and 3 times for final mixing), and several 5-minute incubation periods with magnetic engagement for proper bead separation. Make sure to move plates between the magnetic module and slot 1 as indicated during the pauses, and allow 2-second waits after transfers to ensure complete liquid handling.",
